{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3148409,"name":"Peter","username":"BeastieWaffles","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/beastiewaffles/{size}/182272_2.png","created_at":"2023-02-19T03:06:17.709Z","cooked":"

This coming Tuesday our team will finally receive our Falcon 500 motors. Given the abundance of manufacturing flaws that I have seen with these motors on CD (no Loctite, broken magnets, wiggly shafts, and more) we want to thoroughly inspect our motors before using them on anything.

Could someone please give us a check list for everything we need to inspect on our motors? I unfortunately don’t remember if they are v2s or v3s, so one for each would be incredibly appreciated.

Thanks!
